{
  "name": "Ghoul Adjustment",
  "type": "action",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Ghoul creatures are typically hairless and gaunt with blue or purple skin and pointed ears.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Add the ghoul and undead traits.</li>\n<li>Add the following immunities: death effects, disease, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Paralyzed]{Paralyzed}, poison, @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Unconscious]{Unconscious}.</li>\n<li>Decrease all saving throw modifiers by 1.</li>\n<li style=\"font-weight:bold\"><strong>MANUALLY Add the paralysis ability to the creature's jaws, fangs, or similar <a href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Traits.aspx?ID=199\">unarmed</a> attack. If the creature doesn't have one, add one with the same attack and damage as its strongest melee attack.</strong></li>\n<li>Add the following abilities.</li>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.qCCLZhnp2HhP3Ex6]{Darkvision}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.TTCw5NusiSSkJU1x]{Negative Healing}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-family-ability-glossary.Item.FW4KAUHb7r8WkxUc]{(Ghoul) Paralysis}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-family-ability-glossary.Item.UU1Fp3PRuTFONjC9]{(Ghoul) Swift Leap}</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>"
    },
